cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this code or dataset, please cite it as below."
title: "Managing Intelligence — Experiment 1: the token economics of knowledge work (code + data)"
authors:
  - family-names: Sweatt
    given-names: Mike
    affiliation: TetradStudios
type: dataset
version: 1.0.0
date-released: 2026-07-04
license: MIT
abstract: >-
  Pre-registered experiments measuring the token economics of LLM knowledge
  work: within-cell cost variance (H1), the causal effect of frozen output
  scaffolds ("skills") on output variance, cost, and quality (H5-H8), and a
  documented LLM-judge calibration failure against a blind human panel.
  Includes the full capture harness, frozen fixtures, raw per-call usage
  records, analysis code, and reports. Code is MIT; data and documents are
  CC BY 4.0 (see LICENSE-DATA).
keywords:
  - token economics
  - LLM cost measurement
  - LLM-as-judge
  - pre-registration
  - prompt scaffolding
